<emphasis id="B90F290DFFD77846798E134DFEA72B5A" bold="true" box="[199,359,1375,1401]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry id="F36CB58FFFD7784678261372FE772B59" box="[367,439,1376,1402]" name="Brazil" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(southeastern coast, Rio de Janeiro to São Paulo) (
<bibRefCitation id="EFEA88EEFFD778467D5A1372FB6A2B59" author="Brown" box="[1043,1194,1376,1402]" pageId="9" pageNumber="16" refString="Brown Jr., K. S. (1992) Borboletas da Serra do Japi: Diversidade, habitats, recursos alimentares e variacao temporal, pp. 142 - 187, 18 figs. In: L. P. C. Morellato (Ed.) Historia natural da Serra do Japi. Ecologia e preservacao de uma area florestal no Sudeste do Brasil. Campinas, Editora da Unicamp / Fapesp." type="book chapter" year="1992">
Brown 
<number id="3DB3E738FFD778467D241372FB6A2B59" box="[1133,1194,1376,1402]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="1992.0">1992</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEA88EEFFD778467DFE1372FF152B81" author="Uehara-Prado" pageId="9" pageNumber="17" refString="Uehara-Prado, M., Freitas, A. V. L., Francini, R. B. &amp; Brown, Jr. K. S. (2004) Guia das borboletas frugivoras da Reserva Estadual do Morro Grande e regiao de Caucaia do Alto, Cotia (Sao Paulo). Biota Neotropica, 4, 1 - 25, 18 pls." type="journal article" year="2004">
Uehara-Prado et al. 
<number id="3DB3E738FFD7784679DE139AFF152B81" box="[151,213,1416,1442]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="2004.0">2004</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, Appendix 
<number id="3DB3E738FFD778467812139AFEA92B81" box="[347,361,1416,1442]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="1.0">1</number>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C361A694FFD77846798E13BDFDF428B1" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC4F51FFFD77846798E13BDFDF428B1" blockId="9.[151,1436,976,1682]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis id="B90F290DFFD77846798E13BDFE802BEA" bold="true" box="[199,320,1455,1481]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFEA88EEFFD77846780013A2FDE92BE9" author="Casagrande" box="[329,553,1456,1482]" pageId="9" pageNumber="16" refString="Casagrande, M. M. (2004) Brassolini. p. 201 - 205. In: J. B. Heppner (ed.). Atlas of Neotropical Lepidoptera. Part 4 A Checklist (ed. by G. Lamas). Association of Tropical Lepidoptera / Scientific publishers, Gainesville. 439 p." type="book chapter" year="2004">
Casagrande (
<number id="3DB3E738FFD7784678AA13A2FDE12BE9" box="[483,545,1456,1482]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="2004.0">2004</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
lists no subspecies for 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B8E9CFFD778467A0B13A2FC612BEA" box="[834,929,1456,1481]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Opoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="syme">
<emphasis id="B90F290DFFD778467A0B13A2FC612BEA" box="[834,929,1456,1481]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">O. syme</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It is unlikely that the specimen described by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEA88EEFFD7784679F713CAFE482BD1" author="Rothshild" box="[190,392,1496,1522]" pageId="9" pageNumber="17" refString="Rothshild, L. W. (1916) Notes on Amathusiidae, Brassolidae, Morphidae, etc., with descriptions of new forms. Novitates zoologicae, 23 (3), 299 - 318, pls. 3 - 6." type="journal article" year="1916">
Rothshild (
<number id="3DB3E738FFD77846780A13CAFE402BD1" box="[323,384,1496,1522]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="1916.0">1916</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
as ssp. 
<emphasis id="B90F290DFFD7784678A513CAFDBD2BD2" box="[492,637,1496,1521]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">colombicola</emphasis>
Rothshild was actually collected in 
<collectingCountry id="F36CB58FFFD778467D7E13CAFB6F2BD1" box="[1079,1199,1496,1522]" name="Colombia" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Colombia</collectingCountry>
. Although the male genitalia is nearly identical to 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B8E9CFFD7784678B61012FDB5283A" box="[511,629,1536,1561]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Opoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sulcius">
<emphasis id="B90F290DFFD7784678B61012FDB5283A" box="[511,629,1536,1561]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">O. sulcius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, differences were found in the female genitalia. 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B8E9CFFD778467DFF1012FAA9283A" box="[1206,1385,1536,1561]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Opoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="syme">
<emphasis id="B90F290DFFD778467DFF1012FAA9283A" box="[1206,1385,1536,1561]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Opoptera syme</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B8E9CFFD7784679DE103AFF282862" box="[151,232,1576,1601]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Opoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sulcius">
<emphasis id="B90F290DFFD7784679DE103AFF282862" box="[151,232,1576,1601]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">sulcius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
seem to co-occur in a few sites along their ranges, such as Campos do Jordão and Reserva Estadual do Morro Grande, Cotia (both in São Paulo state), and Nova Friburgo and Petrópolis (Rio de Janeiro; A.V.L. Freitas and K.S. Brown, pers. comm.).
</paragraph>
